521
00:36:08,535 --> 00:36:09,832
George Wade.

522
00:36:10,004 --> 00:36:12,165
Mrs. Kelson, I presume.

523
00:36:12,339 --> 00:36:13,397
What a pleasure.

524
00:36:18,779 --> 00:36:23,842
Well, I can certainly see
where Lucy gets her stare from.

525
00:36:24,018 --> 00:36:25,952
I'm Larry. It's a pleasure to meet you.

526
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:28,179
Thanks, Larry. Same here.

527
00:36:28,355 --> 00:36:31,188
Thank you for letting Lucy quit.
It certainly made our week.

528
00:36:31,358 --> 00:36:34,020
- Great pleasure.
- We should get back to the office.

529
00:36:34,194 --> 00:36:36,128
- Come on! Have some cake.
- We can't.

530
00:36:36,296 --> 00:36:38,526
We're two blocks from the apartment.

531
00:36:38,699 --> 00:36:39,996
- You live around here?
- Sure.

532
00:36:40,167 --> 00:36:42,635
- What a charming coincidence.
- It won't be charming...

533
00:36:42,803 --> 00:36:47,467
...once you block out the sun
with this condo-hotel monstrosity!

534
00:36:48,709 --> 00:36:51,303
We will have a sun deck.

535
00:36:53,047 --> 00:36:55,242
That's something, isn't it?

536
00:36:55,482 --> 00:36:59,213
Larry, Ruth, I can't tell you how much
I appreciate your support on this project.

537
00:36:59,386 --> 00:37:02,219
